FBIS4-40468 "drsov117_b_94020" FBIS-SOV-94-117 Daily Report 16 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military & Nuclear Issues Expedition to Sunken Komsomolets Sub Starts 16 Jun Expedition to Sunken Komsomolets Sub Starts 16 Jun PM1706084394 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 16 Jun 94 p 1 PM1706084394 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA Russian BFN [Report from Own Information-RIA Column: "By Mir to the Komsomolets"] [Text] Kaliningrad -- On board the scientific research ship Akademik Mstislav Keldysh in the Norwegian Sea the preparations for the fourth international expedition to the Komsomolets nuclear submarine have been completed. The ship has Mir apparatuses aboard, which will enable the research staff to reach a depth of 6,000 meters. "The expedition is beginning on 16 June and will take two months. Our main task is to obtain new data on the present condition of the submarine, guarantee its safety in terms of radioactivity, and install new one-year observation stations," Oleg Kuznetsov, the expedition's deputy chief, said.
